{
  "texts": [
    "RepresentationFor CD, chromosomes are represented by vectors consisting of 15 numerical values.",
    "These values encode the movement vectors for two cylinders and the spatial coordinates of all three objects (two cylinders and one box) within the environment.• First 3 Numbers (Indices 0-2): Represent the movement vector of Cylinder 1 in the x, y, and z dimensions, respectively.",
    "This vector indi-cates the intended direction and magnitude of movement for Cylinder 1 in each axis.• Second 3 Numbers (Indices 3-5): Analogously, these encode the movement vector of Cylinder 2 in the x, y, and z dimensions, dictating its intended movement within the space.• Remaining 9 Numbers (Indices 6-14) These are divided into three sets of three numbers each, detailing the current positions of Cylinder 1, Cylinder 2, and the Box, in that order.",
    "Each set provides the x, y, and z coordinates of the respective object, specifying its location in the threedimensional environment.",
    "Operators• Mutation: In the mutation phase, each number within the set of 15 undergoes mutation with an equal probability."
  ]
}